Here's what was fixed and changed:

Bug fix — React is not defined: The issue was a race condition. The app's <script> block ran immediately after the CDN <script src> tags, but the React UMD bundles hadn't finished loading yet in some environments. Two changes resolve this reliably:

Switched to the production minified builds (react.production.min.js / react-dom.production.min.js) with the crossorigin attribute, which load faster and more consistently.
Wrapped the entire app code in window.onload = function() { ... } — this guarantees React and ReactDOM are fully parsed and available as globals before any app code touches them.
Label change: All four instances of "RecordLink" across the page title, dashboard header, login screen, and register screen are now "Record Share".


